metadata.name: The Beauty of Discord #119
metadata.description:
This experimental artwork is a unique blend of human and machine inputs, showcasing the potential for collaboration between the two in the creative process. The human component of the piece is evident in the deliberate composition, choice of color, and the use of painting algorithms. Meanwhile, the machine component is represented by two powerful AI technologies. The first, ChatGPT3, generated a thought-provoking poem about the galaxies and cosmos, serving as the inspiration for the piece. The second, DALL-E 2, then used this poem as a prompt to create a stunning AI image, bringing the cosmic themes to life in a realistic and captivating way.

The combination of these two AI technologies, along with the human touch in the painting algorithms and composition, creates an artwork that is truly one-of-a-kind. The final product is not only visually stunning, but it also serves as a glimpse into the future of humanity and the possibilities of AI collaboration in art. The artwork is a testament to the beauty that can result from a seemingly discordant combination of human and machine inputs, and it invites us to consider the impact of technology on the creative process and the role of the human artist in the age of AI.

Artist notes:
Press s to download high-res images.
Press a to see the AI-generated image.
Press g to switch back to the paint.

metadata.description:

There are two type of objects: eaters and food.
Each eater have own speed and range of vision.
Each eater so hungry that can only seeking food and move to closest food object. They have no time to think and predict future. Only greedy competition.
Each food object have energy which depend on size.
Need for food is fundament of economy.
This program shows simplest scenarios of resource deficient and inequality of possibilities.

metadata.name: Shapes on a Plane #268
metadata.description:
“Shapes on a Plane” explores imaginary structures and worlds through simple shapes. It’s intended for small-scale print.

As a kid I was obsessed with Lego, Duplo, wooden building blocks... anything I could make something with.

I’d spend hours building things, imagining new worlds, new machines, new concepts, then i’d take them apart and create a whole new idea to explore.

To me, this piece to me is a reminder of that time - many days spent exploring ideas with those simple objects - no care for viability, for marketability, for audiences or business. Just pure fun.

Without this time in my life, I doubt I’d have found my passion for creating in the way I do today.

metadata.name: (recombination/perspectives)-I: Horizons #16
metadata.description:
🌊 🌞 🌈 🌅


    ( r e c o m b i n a t i o n  /  p e r s p e c t i v e s ) 


                     I :   H o r i z o n s


                            ✨ 🧬 🧡 ⏲







-----
* What/How *

2 560 000 particles are subjected to a succession of 64 energy bursts which scatters the points through space. 
The algorithm then stores 3 configurations of points, forming an entangled coherent system.
After few seconds multiple observation modalities are then selected sequentially to allow for dynamic and contemplative visualization.

-----
* Mint preview *

Minter will get a 2160x2160 PNG bitmap and an infinite randomly deterministic animation.

-----
* Technics *

This experience is designed to be executed on a recent GPU (>2016) and displayed on 16/9 screens from FHD to 8K+ (1920x1080 → 7680x4320) at 60FPS for infinite duration.

- JavaScript / ThreeJS / WebGL / GLSL
- Unique generative, random and determinist animation (animation is seeded by the fxhash mint hash)
- Infinite animation
- Animation sequences duration between 6 and 60 seconds.

-----
* Controls *

Keyboard "Space" : take a PNG capture of the current view frame (same ratio as window, max 1920x1080)

Keyboard "X" : skip current animation sequence / next sequence

-----
* URL modifiers *

"&fastdemo=on"
Forces animation sequences to last 10 seconds instead of random durations.

"&slow=on"
Forces animation sequences to last 1 minute instead of random durations.

"&static=on"
Disables animation automatic start. Press "X" to start animations.


-----
@HAL09999 – January 25th, 2023

metadata.name: inlim:in #250
metadata.description:
"inlim:in" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at PARIS+ par Art Basel

Atemporal iridescent fragments of the in between. The series is inspired by the many liminal spaces and unseen influences that permeate the visible universe and its participants. Created with GLSL, every piece of the series is generated using the space around the visible object to cast its shape. The series creates a gentle and colorful expanse through which viewers might contemplate what it is to exist at an infinite threshold.

metadata.name: Sketch F #555
metadata.description:
Sketch is an open-ended series. Works evolve as I code a generative project, sometimes drastically. Intermediate works usually don't see the light of day - they get archived and forgotten. This series is snapshots of different forms along the way - each standing alone, but also part of a larger meandering work flow. The word Sketch implies incompleteness. This project may end up being two works, or it could evolve for years. Part of the joy of generative art is never knowing what's around the corner. I have no set schedule. There may be multiple Sketches released a week, or it could be weeks or months between drops. I have no idea where Sketch is heading and there is no guarantee of cohesiveness from Sketch to Sketch. Color palettes and forms will change as new ideas are explored.

Sketch F(ree). A gift to all Sketch A-E collectors. The underlying grid structure from A-E remains, but more variation on size and distribution is added. Many more color palettes are introduced. Grid size, padding, and colors vary.

metadata.name: Tenements #16
metadata.description:
"Some we see no more, Tenements of Wonder
Occupy to us though perhaps to them
Simpler are the Days than the Supposition
Leave us to presume

That oblique Belief which we call Conjecture
Grapples with a Theme stubborn as Sublime
Able as the Dust to equip its feature
Adequate as Drums
To enlist the Tomb."   (Emily Dickinson )

A moody depiction of cursed tenements in a rainy city. Anxious residents racked by fevered dreams peer out of uncertain windows, while phantoms and figments prowl the lower floors.

[Plain javascript with curated window and graffiti images generated by a neural network (VQGAN+Clip)]

metadata.name: Winter Lake #13
metadata.description:
<<Anyway, il n’y avait rien, IL N’Y A RIEN tout court. Là on le voit. Là on le sait. On est tout nus dans la neige. On est vraiment un vide, un vrai vide, un qui aspire, un vacuum et ce vide garde tout le temps sa force de vide, sa faim douloureuse. Ça dévore tout à mesure, nous avec. On est un vide qui se refait, c’est ça notre sens, et on est contents. C’est pédant mais c’est ça qui est ça. On se laissera pas faire, chère, Woffe and toffe !>>  de <<L’hiver de force>> de Réjean Ducharme

A depiction of the bleakness and beauty of a Quebec winter, showing a frozen lake stretching off into the cold distance. Hints of storm clouds and the Northern Lights are visible, along with the occasional lone ice-fishing shack. L'hiver est une camisole de force...


[Vanilla javascript, with textures generated by a neural network decoder ported to javascript using ONNX Runtime Web]

metadata.name: Badgirs City #99
metadata.description:
"I used to live in a small city placed at the center of Iran's plateau with the warmest summer days in the country part; spending most of my childhood with my sweet grandma at her old house. She was always keeping her eyes on me not to get heat stroke at noon playing in the yard when the sun was at its peak glowing furiously. Sundays at noon were my favorite, I used to call them “Ice cream” noons sitting beside the nicest person you could imagine and enjoying a delightful ice cream. You won't know how lovely it was to have an ice cream relaxing under the most enjoyable cold breeze of the tallest windcatcher in the city at her house. "



The Badgirs city is the first collaboration between Fleep and IceRain on Fxhash. The concept was established first with the design of a school with a feeling of safe and nostalgia reminding us of the good memories of our childhood as the grandma’s house and the windcatcher for Fleep.
A windcatcher (Badgir) is an Iranian traditional architectural element in the form of a small tower built on the roof of houses in warm locations to create passive cooling. The collection of Badgirs city is a modern recreational development of those traditional windcatchers designed by Fleep and icerain and exquisitely translated into code by Icerain.

Controls:
[1] Set the resolution to Medium Resolution
[2] Set the resolution to High Resolution

metadata.name: WatSplash #4
metadata.description:
Water Splash is a stunning piece of art that captures the beauty and "movement" of watercolors, the piece features multiple drops of watercolors as it falls from a "faucet" and creates a splash upon impact. The bright colors and bold brushstrokes used in the painting add to its dynamism and energy.

Overall, Water Splash is a breathtaking work of art that is sure to impress and inspire.

I hope you enjoy it!
